                <msContents>
                  
                    <summary>19th century prayers of magical character</summary>
                   
                    <textLang mainLang="gez" source="IANA">Ge'ez</textLang>
                    
                    <msItem n="1" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_15_1">
                        <locus from="1" to="82">Lines 1-82</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer against Barya, Legewon, chest pain, rheumatism, vaginal haemorrhage and <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->, and the legend of St. Susenyos and Warzelya</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Line 1</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                        
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, barya are a people believed to serve the demon or spirit provoking epilepsy and therefore barya is identified with this disease. Legewon is a name for Satan, chief of the barya and 
                            one of the most frequently occurring devils in Ethiopic magical literature (<ref>Strelcyn</ref>).</note>   
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="2" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_15_2">
                        <locus from="83" to="126">Lines 83-126</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer for expelling demons</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Line 83</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="3" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_15_3">
                        <locus from="126" to="156">Lines 126-156</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Salam to Archangel Phanuel, the expeller of demons</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Line 126</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="4" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_15_4">
                        <locus from="157" to="177">Lines 157-177</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer against vaginal haemorrhage and <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing--></title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Line 157</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                        
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing--> is a devil who makes women sterile, causes spontaneous abortion and attacks suckling infants (<ref>Strelcyn</ref>).</note>   
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="5" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_15_5">
                        <locus from="177" to="198">Lines 177-198</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer against <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing--> and pleurisy</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Line 177</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                        
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing--> is colic with a bad stomach ache as well as the demon of the threshold and of the closed door (<ref>Strelcyn</ref>).</note>   
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="6" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_15_6">
